1
00:02:51,706 --> 00:02:52,556
Go back!

2
00:02:52,581 --> 00:02:54,792
Consider this
our first official case together.

3
00:02:55,184 --> 00:02:56,602
According here…

4
00:02:57,191 --> 00:03:02,446
Isaac texted three people
with the same message.

5
00:03:04,315 --> 00:03:05,733
It was you, Genesis.

6
00:03:10,905 --> 00:03:12,156
What happened to him?

7
00:03:12,298 --> 00:03:15,644
Does that mean
he was killed to silence him?

8
00:03:17,537 --> 00:03:18,830
Lorelei Rios?

9
00:03:19,747 --> 00:03:22,082
Do you know Loki’s favorite song?

10
00:03:22,083 --> 00:03:27,504
♪ Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star ♪

11
00:03:27,505 --> 00:03:29,882
♪ How I wonder... ♪

12
00:03:29,883 --> 00:03:31,134
I said stop!

13
00:04:01,039 --> 00:04:02,874
Help!

14
00:04:04,876 --> 00:04:07,003
Is someone there?

15
00:04:33,029 --> 00:04:34,656
Help!

16
00:04:59,681 --> 00:05:01,518
Help!

17
00:05:16,406 --> 00:05:18,282
You’re finally awake!

18
00:05:19,867 --> 00:05:22,286
Did you enjoy your afternoon nap?

19
00:05:25,187 --> 00:05:26,252
Maggie?

20
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:28,041
Wait…

21
00:05:28,258 --> 00:05:30,135
Were you the one
who had me kidnapped?

22
00:05:30,878 --> 00:05:32,380
What does this mean?

23
00:05:32,714 --> 00:05:34,456
Why do you have to do this to me?

24
00:05:34,674 --> 00:05:36,092
Are you out of your mind?

25
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:38,250
You’re so damn stubborn!

26
00:05:39,178 --> 00:05:40,972
I already warned you about him!

27
00:05:41,472 --> 00:05:43,182
Loki is dangerous.

28
00:05:43,474 --> 00:05:44,885
But you didn’t listen!

29
00:05:44,916 --> 00:05:47,251
Well, sorry for being stubborn!

30
00:05:47,603 --> 00:05:51,732
If you think you can force me to do
something I don't want,

31
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:53,192
you’d be disappointed!

32
00:05:53,901 --> 00:05:57,071
I guess you leave me
with no other option but to improvise.

33
00:05:57,488 --> 00:05:58,656
Improvise?

34
00:05:58,866 --> 00:06:01,160
God! You remind me of my father.

35
00:06:01,701 --> 00:06:03,119
You two think alike.

36
00:06:03,453 --> 00:06:05,704
You both think
that you’ve control over me,

37
00:06:05,705 --> 00:06:06,748
but you don't.

38
00:06:07,081 --> 00:06:09,250
Sorry, but I do what I do!

39
00:06:09,542 --> 00:06:11,044
Go ahead, lose your minds!

40
00:06:11,249 --> 00:06:12,250
Okay.

41
00:06:13,150 --> 00:06:14,193
Let’s see…

42
00:06:15,131 --> 00:06:18,182
if someone’s going to save
a damsel in distress.

43
00:06:18,676 --> 00:06:20,303
That dress really suits you.

44
00:06:24,474 --> 00:06:26,323
We gave Loki fifteen minutes.

45
00:06:26,684 --> 00:06:27,935
If he finds you…

46
00:06:28,144 --> 00:06:30,271
we’ll let you stay at the club.

47
00:06:30,719 --> 00:06:33,292
And I would promise
not to bother you about it anymore.

48
00:06:34,150 --> 00:06:36,611
But if he doesn’t show up in time…

49
00:06:36,861 --> 00:06:38,905
that’s a sign for you to quit the club.

50
00:06:39,906 --> 00:06:42,628
Knowing that you two
are not in good terms...

51
00:06:43,242 --> 00:06:44,577
I’m wondering...

52
00:06:45,411 --> 00:06:48,289
how would Loki respond to this challenge?

53
00:06:52,919 --> 00:06:55,587
No! No! No!

54
00:06:55,588 --> 00:06:58,381
No! No! No!

55
00:06:58,382 --> 00:07:00,343
No, Maggie!

56
00:07:02,053 --> 00:07:03,096
Anyway,

57
00:07:03,304 --> 00:07:06,432
while you’re waiting,
you can try to crack that code.

58
00:07:06,724 --> 00:07:08,350
After ten minutes,

59
00:07:08,351 --> 00:07:12,271
if he still can’t find you,
my teammates will come get you.

60
00:07:12,688 --> 00:07:16,818
By then, I hope you’d realize
that he doesn’t care about you at all.

61
00:07:20,488 --> 00:07:22,156
That’s enough, Maggie!

62
00:07:34,335 --> 00:07:36,254
♪ Shadows ♪

63
00:07:36,546 --> 00:07:39,257
♪ Creeping slowly through the dark ♪

64
00:07:39,888 --> 00:07:43,933
♪ Watching, blocking, like ♪

65
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:47,504
♪ You can't even take a step ♪

66
00:07:48,028 --> 00:07:51,580
♪ Every cry, every shake ♪

67
00:07:51,727 --> 00:07:54,981
♪ Only walls reflect the ache ♪

68
00:07:55,006 --> 00:07:57,967
♪ All the echoes burn inside ♪

69
00:07:57,992 --> 00:08:02,496
♪ Like fire and bullets in the past ♪

70
00:08:03,794 --> 00:08:06,176
♪ Listen to the warnings ♪

71
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:09,628
♪ Threats are drawing near ♪

72
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:14,395
♪ This is not the world you thought ♪

73
00:08:14,878 --> 00:08:17,380
♪ You would know ♪

74
00:08:17,405 --> 00:08:19,866
♪ Listen to the warnings ♪

75
00:08:20,788 --> 00:08:22,915
♪ Open up your eyes ♪

76
00:08:24,192 --> 00:08:27,737
♪ This is not the world you thought ♪

77
00:08:28,603 --> 00:08:31,278
♪ You would know ♪

78
00:08:31,303 --> 00:08:36,141
♪ Listen to the warnings ♪

79
00:08:48,757 --> 00:08:50,301
Fifteen minutes…

80
00:08:59,086 --> 00:09:01,797
I guess it’s been about five minutes
since I got my coffee.

81
00:09:03,424 --> 00:09:07,345
Someone must have slipped this card
onto my table while I was away.

82
00:09:08,888 --> 00:09:10,806
Now I only have ten minutes.

83
00:09:17,188 --> 00:09:18,940
Don’t you have other things to do?

84
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:20,774
If Loki’s mind is still sharp,

85
00:09:20,775 --> 00:09:23,152
it’s just a matter of minutes,
he'll be here.

86
00:09:24,278 --> 00:09:26,113
What if he catches you here?

87
00:09:27,615 --> 00:09:29,951
Sorry, I got carried away.

88
00:09:31,994 --> 00:09:34,997
So, we’ll leave you here for now.

89
00:09:35,248 --> 00:09:37,083
Pray that your savior shows up.

90
00:10:16,205 --> 00:10:18,749
Will Loki find me in time?

91
00:10:19,583 --> 00:10:22,753
Or am I just assuming he’ll look for me?

92
00:10:23,254 --> 00:10:26,090
He’s too absorbed in his own world.

93
00:10:27,008 --> 00:10:29,093
Would he even bother to look for me?

94
00:10:32,096 --> 00:10:34,724
Why did I end up in this situation?

95
00:10:35,641 --> 00:10:38,894
Maybe I’ve caught Loki’s bad luck too.

96
00:10:40,271 --> 00:10:42,940
Is this the effect
of me being close to him?

97
00:11:05,963 --> 00:11:08,341
If he doesn’t come looking for me,

98
00:11:08,674 --> 00:11:10,468
maybe Maggie was right,

99
00:11:10,843 --> 00:11:13,220
I should leave the Q.E.D. Club.

100
00:12:04,313 --> 00:12:05,313
Lorelei!

101
00:12:05,398 --> 00:12:06,482
Lorelei, are you okay?

102
00:12:07,024 --> 00:12:08,025
Did they hurt you?

103
00:12:08,484 --> 00:12:10,194
Hey, are you okay?

104
00:12:13,447 --> 00:12:14,365
Ouch!

105
00:12:14,366 --> 00:12:16,242
Slow down there!

106
00:12:18,869 --> 00:12:20,704
Apologies for merely trying to help.

107
00:12:26,752 --> 00:12:28,629
I thought something bad happened to you.

108
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,173
I was so worried.

109
00:12:34,802 --> 00:12:35,802
Ouch.

110
00:12:40,224 --> 00:12:42,435
First aid kit, you need this.

111
00:12:50,025 --> 00:12:51,026
Be careful.

112
00:12:53,279 --> 00:12:54,280
Here.

113
00:12:55,239 --> 00:12:56,239
It hurts!

114
00:12:56,657 --> 00:12:57,408
What?

115
00:12:57,409 --> 00:12:58,451
I’ll do it!

116
00:13:13,048 --> 00:13:15,843
How did you even find out
where I was taken?

117
00:13:19,555 --> 00:13:20,555
Well…

118
00:13:21,724 --> 00:13:23,601
someone left this card on my table.

119
00:13:25,561 --> 00:13:27,313
Claiming that they’ve abducted you.

120
00:13:28,898 --> 00:13:30,441
At first, I thought it was a joke.

121
00:13:32,902 --> 00:13:35,070
Until I saw the symbol
at the back of the card.

122
00:13:38,324 --> 00:13:40,034
I cracked the code in just two minutes.

123
00:13:40,618 --> 00:13:41,619
Two minutes?

124
00:13:43,078 --> 00:13:44,104
How?

125
00:13:46,332 --> 00:13:47,791
Through Caesar’s Box.

126
00:13:49,335 --> 00:13:53,130
You will count the number of characters
in the code.

127
00:13:53,797 --> 00:13:55,132
How many letters?

128
00:13:55,883 --> 00:13:56,884
Sixteen.

129
00:13:57,218 --> 00:13:58,218
Okay.

130
00:13:58,469 --> 00:13:59,845
What’s the square root of 16?

131
00:14:00,554 --> 00:14:01,597
Four.

132
00:14:01,805 --> 00:14:02,805
Okay.

133
00:14:03,307 --> 00:14:06,268
Now we write out the characters
into four rows,

134
00:14:06,685 --> 00:14:07,853
four letters.

135
00:14:09,063 --> 00:14:10,856
From left to right.

136
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:14,610
Now, start from top left,

137
00:14:15,194 --> 00:14:16,570
and read down,

138
00:14:17,154 --> 00:14:18,948
then continue to the next column.

139
00:14:19,907 --> 00:14:21,158
What did you read?

140
00:14:22,409 --> 00:14:23,827
In the costume room.

141
00:14:26,163 --> 00:14:27,306
Wow.

142
00:14:27,331 --> 00:14:29,291
I didn’t think of the Caesar’s Box.

143
00:14:32,503 --> 00:14:35,089
I need to bring this card
to the campus police

144
00:14:35,881 --> 00:14:38,133
and check if whoever sent this thing

145
00:14:38,528 --> 00:14:40,177
left their fingerprints.

146
00:14:40,928 --> 00:14:42,747
Wait, Loki...

147
00:14:43,222 --> 00:14:45,641
I know who kidnapped me now.

148
00:14:46,308 --> 00:14:47,851
She talked to me earlier.

149
00:14:48,352 --> 00:14:51,814
Actually, she also gave me
a copy of that card.

150
00:14:54,024 --> 00:14:55,251
Who?

151
00:14:55,276 --> 00:14:57,069
It’s Maggie Fernandez.

152
00:14:57,611 --> 00:14:59,655
The one I mentioned to you the other day.

153
00:15:05,661 --> 00:15:07,538
I knew it. I knew it!

154
00:15:08,330 --> 00:15:09,389
Wait...

155
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,711
isn't that an "M" logo?

156
00:15:13,252 --> 00:15:14,336
Could it be...

157
00:15:14,795 --> 00:15:16,797
she’s the M you were talking about?

158
00:15:18,215 --> 00:15:19,425
What if…

159
00:15:20,259 --> 00:15:22,928
Maggie is involved with M?

160
00:15:23,476 --> 00:15:25,645
Or M is Maggie?

161
00:15:26,348 --> 00:15:29,059
Because her name starts with the letter M.

162
00:15:29,992 --> 00:15:31,035
I don’t know.

163
00:15:31,353 --> 00:15:32,771
Its just a theory.

164
00:15:33,689 --> 00:15:36,441
This game is ridiculously easy

165
00:15:36,442 --> 00:15:37,803
for the real M to have made it.

166
00:15:42,869 --> 00:15:44,996
How dare he use M to trick me?

167
00:15:45,409 --> 00:15:46,452
He?

168
00:15:46,660 --> 00:15:47,828
Maggie is a woman!

169
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,221
No.

170
00:15:49,246 --> 00:15:50,623
She’s only a pawn.

171
00:15:50,815 --> 00:15:52,692
There’s another person behind this.

172
00:15:53,334 --> 00:15:55,461
The person behind your abduction...

173
00:15:56,879 --> 00:15:58,797
is someone who reeks of evil

174
00:15:59,048 --> 00:16:00,799
and relentless manipulation.

175
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:11,267
Is he tall

176
00:16:11,268 --> 00:16:13,312
and has creepy voice?

177
00:16:16,231 --> 00:16:17,316
Did you see him?

178
00:16:17,816 --> 00:16:18,901
No.

179
00:16:19,610 --> 00:16:23,989
I only saw his silhouette,
but I heard his voice.

180
00:16:24,448 --> 00:16:25,449
Why?

181
00:16:26,241 --> 00:16:27,826
Do you know who he is?

182
00:16:32,873 --> 00:16:35,042
I’d rather not meet him if I were you.

183
00:16:38,128 --> 00:16:41,156
If you think I’m bad,

184
00:16:42,257 --> 00:16:43,550
he’s worse.

185
00:16:45,969 --> 00:16:49,055
Since I already know who kidnapped me,

186
00:16:49,056 --> 00:16:51,849
we should report it
to the Office of Student Affairs.

187
00:16:51,850 --> 00:16:55,604
So Maggie and that tall guy
will stop messing with me!

188
00:16:55,979 --> 00:16:57,063
No need.

189
00:16:57,064 --> 00:16:58,940
Huh? Why?

190
00:16:58,941 --> 00:17:00,025
Trust me.

191
00:17:01,694 --> 00:17:03,654
All your efforts will go to waste.

192
00:17:04,363 --> 00:17:06,156
Whatever you tell OSA,

193
00:17:06,949 --> 00:17:08,325
it won’t go anywhere.

194
00:17:08,575 --> 00:17:09,910
It’ll just get dismissed.

195
00:17:10,369 --> 00:17:11,411
So, what?

196
00:17:11,412 --> 00:17:12,870
That's it?

197
00:17:12,871 --> 00:17:14,956
After they put me to sleep,

198
00:17:14,957 --> 00:17:16,333
tied my hands,

199
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,085
and covered my mouth?

200
00:17:18,460 --> 00:17:19,669
Sorry, Loki!

201
00:17:19,670 --> 00:17:21,379
But I won’t let that slide!

202
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:23,924
I’m not saying we should let
what happened to you slide.

203
00:17:24,508 --> 00:17:25,801
I’m just telling you...

204
00:17:26,635 --> 00:17:30,597
don’t waste any time and effort
in something so futile.

205
00:17:31,265 --> 00:17:32,808
If you want to report this,

206
00:17:32,933 --> 00:17:34,435
I won’t stop you.

207
00:17:34,893 --> 00:17:36,311
But just so you know,

208
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:40,415
they have high positions
and influence at school.

209
00:17:41,567 --> 00:17:43,152
They’ll just get away with it.

210
00:17:46,989 --> 00:17:49,408
Not everyone here can be trusted.

211
00:17:51,910 --> 00:17:53,955
Even those you consider friends.

212
00:17:57,040 --> 00:18:00,611
We have to be more careful
and strategic with our actions.

213
00:18:05,132 --> 00:18:06,133
By the way,

214
00:18:08,177 --> 00:18:09,595
that dress looks good on you.

215
00:18:11,054 --> 00:18:12,556
But you might need to change…

216
00:18:13,474 --> 00:18:16,059
you might cause unwanted attention
along the way.

217
00:18:21,356 --> 00:18:22,408
Loki…

218
00:18:23,525 --> 00:18:25,235
before I forget,

219
00:18:26,612 --> 00:18:28,822
thanks for saving me earlier.

220
00:18:35,329 --> 00:18:37,916
Not everyone here can be trusted.

221
00:18:38,582 --> 00:18:40,470
Even your so-called friends.

222
00:18:41,272 --> 00:18:44,817
We need to be careful
and strategic with our actions.

223
00:18:46,423 --> 00:18:53,478
Why does Loki think like that?
Am I safe here at Clark U?

224
00:19:04,942 --> 00:19:06,318
Yes, Loki?

225
00:19:06,527 --> 00:19:07,527
Why?

226
00:19:07,736 --> 00:19:08,987
What do you need?

227
00:19:10,489 --> 00:19:11,532
First of all,

228
00:19:12,991 --> 00:19:15,244
I apologize for my reaction last time.

229
00:19:15,869 --> 00:19:17,538
That was totally uncalled for.

230
00:19:18,372 --> 00:19:20,958
Aren’t you just being forced to say sorry?

231
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:24,126
Because if you're not ready to, then...

232
00:19:24,127 --> 00:19:25,127
No!

233
00:19:25,712 --> 00:19:26,712
This time,

234
00:19:27,756 --> 00:19:29,216
it’s a genuine apology.

235
00:19:30,968 --> 00:19:32,219
I’m saying sorry…

236
00:19:32,427 --> 00:19:33,762
because I’m really sorry.

237
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:38,183
Actually,

238
00:19:39,101 --> 00:19:41,270
I should apologize to you too.

239
00:19:41,854 --> 00:19:44,898
I became insensitive
to your feelings back then.

240
00:19:46,275 --> 00:19:48,610
Sorry for talking too much.

241
00:19:49,570 --> 00:19:50,904
Apology accepted.

242
00:19:55,784 --> 00:19:56,784
Now,

243
00:19:57,077 --> 00:19:59,120
I’d like to take this opportunity

244
00:19:59,121 --> 00:20:01,875
to ask you,
if you still like to stay in this club.

245
00:20:04,251 --> 00:20:05,251
Rhea,

246
00:20:06,879 --> 00:20:08,297
the last member I had,

247
00:20:08,839 --> 00:20:09,923
was killed

248
00:20:11,054 --> 00:20:12,551
because she was linked to me.

249
00:20:14,553 --> 00:20:16,096
It’s my responsibility

250
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,015
to look for M

251
00:20:18,098 --> 00:20:19,766
and bring him to justice.

252
00:20:20,809 --> 00:20:21,935
The problem is,

253
00:20:22,519 --> 00:20:25,939
anyone close to me
could get caught up looking for M.

254
00:20:28,066 --> 00:20:29,117
Well,

255
00:20:29,236 --> 00:20:30,529
I’m already here.

256
00:20:31,486 --> 00:20:32,820
I’m already involved.

257
00:20:32,821 --> 00:20:33,864
So…

258
00:20:35,157 --> 00:20:38,702
I’m not backing out
of something I started.

259
00:20:40,078 --> 00:20:40,954
You know,

260
00:20:41,079 --> 00:20:44,416
Maggie did warn me about the dangers
of joining your club.

261
00:20:46,126 --> 00:20:47,628
But I don’t care anymore.

262
00:20:48,587 --> 00:20:49,962
I’ll face everything,

263
00:20:49,963 --> 00:20:52,340
and I’ll try to survive,

264
00:20:52,341 --> 00:20:53,675
as long as I can.

265
00:20:54,134 --> 00:20:55,235
Right?

266
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,845
And the truth is,

267
00:20:57,596 --> 00:20:59,431
over the past few months,

268
00:21:00,307 --> 00:21:03,114
I’ve done nothing but run

269
00:21:03,435 --> 00:21:06,438
from all the chaos
and problems in my life.

270
00:21:07,981 --> 00:21:09,724
But I don’t wanna run anymore.

271
00:21:13,487 --> 00:21:14,863
If that’s your decision,

272
00:21:15,697 --> 00:21:17,240
I’d gladly accept it.

273
00:21:19,618 --> 00:21:20,619
Well then...

274
00:21:22,287 --> 00:21:26,124
To our brand new partnership
as members of the Q.E.D. Club.

275
00:21:30,963 --> 00:21:31,996
Good night.

276
00:21:33,452 --> 00:21:34,519
Good night.

277
00:21:51,149 --> 00:21:52,355
Lori!

278
00:21:57,823 --> 00:21:59,658
Lori? Dear?

279
00:22:20,012 --> 00:22:21,012
Yuck!

280
00:22:46,997 --> 00:22:48,081
Tita Martha?

281
00:22:48,582 --> 00:22:51,793
What’s going on? Why are you cleaning?

282
00:22:52,335 --> 00:22:53,419
Morning!

283
00:22:53,420 --> 00:22:54,712
Hey, good morning.

284
00:22:54,713 --> 00:22:55,922
"What's going on?"

285
00:22:56,381 --> 00:22:57,381
Yes.

286
00:22:57,424 --> 00:22:58,550
Garbage.

287
00:22:59,134 --> 00:23:00,134
Mess.

288
00:23:00,343 --> 00:23:02,470
So much mess. That’s hilarious.

289
00:23:02,471 --> 00:23:03,513
Sorry about that.

290
00:23:04,139 --> 00:23:05,264
Come on!

291
00:23:05,265 --> 00:23:07,434
Didn’t I tell you last week,

292
00:23:07,559 --> 00:23:09,143
that your Papa’s coming...

293
00:23:09,144 --> 00:23:10,144
today.

294
00:23:10,187 --> 00:23:11,187
Huh?

295
00:23:11,229 --> 00:23:13,940
As in, he's coming today?

296
00:23:14,024 --> 00:23:14,900
Yes!

297
00:23:15,025 --> 00:23:16,275
As in, today.

298
00:23:16,276 --> 00:23:18,445
Not yesterday, not tomorrow, but today!

299
00:23:18,653 --> 00:23:20,571
This is so embarrassing for your Papa,

300
00:23:20,572 --> 00:23:24,784
seeing how messy
his only daughter’s unit is.

301
00:23:24,785 --> 00:23:26,244
That's why I'm cleaning it.

302
00:23:26,745 --> 00:23:29,790
He might be here this afternoon,
so go home early, okay?

303
00:23:29,915 --> 00:23:31,208
Okay.

304
00:23:32,292 --> 00:23:33,292
Okay.

305
00:23:34,294 --> 00:23:36,797
Are you embarrassed that I’m cleaning?

306
00:23:37,631 --> 00:23:38,923
A little bit.

307
00:23:38,924 --> 00:23:40,633
- I’ll take care of it.
- Alright!

308
00:23:40,634 --> 00:23:44,096
- Okay, okay, okay. Go ahead.
- Alright.

309
00:24:02,948 --> 00:24:04,074
You look troubled.

310
00:24:05,117 --> 00:24:06,576
Is there something bothering you?

311
00:24:07,410 --> 00:24:08,662
How did you say that?

312
00:24:09,704 --> 00:24:11,206
Is it obvious on my face?

313
00:24:12,582 --> 00:24:13,582
First,

314
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,710
you can’t sit still in your spot.

315
00:24:16,128 --> 00:24:17,170
Second,

316
00:24:18,171 --> 00:24:19,965
since you came into the office,

317
00:24:21,174 --> 00:24:23,760
I’ve already heard you sigh six times.

318
00:24:24,970 --> 00:24:25,970
Apparently,

319
00:24:26,346 --> 00:24:29,224
you’ve been trying to shake off
whatever it is that’s bothering you.

320
00:24:29,808 --> 00:24:31,017
But, unfortunately,

321
00:24:31,351 --> 00:24:32,727
you’re not very good at it.

322
00:24:33,562 --> 00:24:34,562
So...

323
00:24:34,938 --> 00:24:36,273
what is bothering you?

324
00:24:38,733 --> 00:24:39,733
Fine!

325
00:24:39,860 --> 00:24:41,736
Well, since you're asking,

326
00:24:42,070 --> 00:24:43,405
I’ll tell you,

327
00:24:43,738 --> 00:24:45,699
even if it’s none of your business.

328
00:24:48,660 --> 00:24:52,122
My Papa’s coming to visit me
at the apartment this afternoon.

329
00:24:52,539 --> 00:24:55,834
Now that explains why the landlady
was cleaning earlier this morning.

330
00:24:58,253 --> 00:24:59,253
Hmm…

331
00:24:59,671 --> 00:25:00,839
I find it odd.

332
00:25:01,715 --> 00:25:03,008
Because for most kids,

333
00:25:03,341 --> 00:25:05,594
a visit from their parents is a good news.

334
00:25:06,678 --> 00:25:07,888
But in your case,

335
00:25:09,556 --> 00:25:10,682
it's the opposite.

336
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:13,977
Do you have issues with your father?

337
00:25:15,770 --> 00:25:16,770
Don’t worry.

338
00:25:16,980 --> 00:25:19,900
I know that feeling
of despising someone related to you.

339
00:25:23,153 --> 00:25:26,573
Sometimes, you just want to cut
all ties with him.

340
00:25:27,365 --> 00:25:29,576
That’s how I strongly I detest my brother.

341
00:25:31,745 --> 00:25:32,829
Just to be clear,

342
00:25:33,413 --> 00:25:35,290
I don’t hate my father.

343
00:25:35,999 --> 00:25:37,751
I don’t despise him either.

344
00:25:38,460 --> 00:25:40,795
Despise is too strong of a word.

345
00:25:42,130 --> 00:25:43,130
Anyway,

346
00:25:43,548 --> 00:25:45,550
I don’t want to see him for now.

347
00:25:47,636 --> 00:25:49,888
Don’t think too much about your father.

348
00:25:50,722 --> 00:25:52,140
The more you think about him,

349
00:25:52,724 --> 00:25:54,100
the more it gets to you.

350
00:25:54,976 --> 00:25:57,520
I wish it were that easy to do.

351
00:25:58,438 --> 00:25:59,438
But it’s not.

352
00:26:00,148 --> 00:26:01,858
That’s a problem with you people.

353
00:26:02,776 --> 00:26:05,070
You worry so much about the inevitable.

354
00:26:06,071 --> 00:26:07,614
If your father visits,

355
00:26:08,198 --> 00:26:09,616
there’s nothing you can do.

356
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:12,285
Just accept that you two will meet.

357
00:26:13,411 --> 00:26:15,538
But if meeting him bothers you that much,

358
00:26:16,581 --> 00:26:17,624
make up an excuse.

359
00:26:18,166 --> 00:26:19,209
Just say,

360
00:26:19,417 --> 00:26:21,544
you have schoolwork, that’s it!

361
00:26:25,131 --> 00:26:26,633
Come on, Lori! Get in!

362
00:26:28,426 --> 00:26:29,761
Welcome to…

363
00:26:30,428 --> 00:26:31,805
The White Hostel!

364
00:26:32,222 --> 00:26:33,305
Nice place.

365
00:26:33,306 --> 00:26:34,431
It's fine, right?

366
00:26:34,432 --> 00:26:35,432
Pretty nice, right?

367
00:26:35,433 --> 00:26:36,433
Yeah.

368
00:26:38,436 --> 00:26:40,229
Sir, good afternoon!

369
00:26:40,230 --> 00:26:41,689
I just have a visitor.

370
00:26:41,690 --> 00:26:43,023
Please sign in, ma’am.

371
00:26:43,024 --> 00:26:44,192
Good afternoon.

372
00:26:53,785 --> 00:26:54,827
Thank you, sir.

373
00:26:54,828 --> 00:26:55,828
Thank you, ma'am.

374
00:26:56,037 --> 00:26:57,871
Hey, Rosetta. Thank you so much.

375
00:26:57,872 --> 00:27:01,041
Sorry, I left my key at my apartment.

376
00:27:01,042 --> 00:27:03,294
My roommate’s not going home
until tonight,

377
00:27:03,295 --> 00:27:05,671
so I’ve got nowhere else to go.

378
00:27:05,672 --> 00:27:08,341
What’s with you?
No problem, as long as it’s you!

379
00:27:09,426 --> 00:27:10,885
- Let’s go?
- Okay.

380
00:27:12,262 --> 00:27:15,681
The nice thing about White Hostel
is you can have visitors.

381
00:27:15,682 --> 00:27:16,725
Please sign in, sir.

382
00:27:17,142 --> 00:27:19,059
So for our presentation,

383
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:22,604
I separated the purpose and legacy
from the main Greek gods.

384
00:27:22,605 --> 00:27:25,734
So we each get a part.
But I’ve already started...

385
00:27:27,027 --> 00:27:28,027
Are you okay?

386
00:27:29,029 --> 00:27:31,864
Yeah, it’s nothing. I’m just sleepy.

387
00:27:31,865 --> 00:27:33,907
Do you want coffee? I have some. You want?

388
00:27:33,908 --> 00:27:36,285
Oh, no need, girl. I’m fine.

389
00:27:36,286 --> 00:27:38,621
Come on, that’s easy. Hold on.

390
00:27:53,595 --> 00:27:54,429
Hello?

391
00:27:54,596 --> 00:27:55,596
Loki?

392
00:27:56,181 --> 00:27:57,181
Why?

393
00:27:57,515 --> 00:27:58,599
Hey, Lorelei.

394
00:27:58,600 --> 00:27:59,600
Are you home?

395
00:28:00,143 --> 00:28:01,853
How was your meeting with your dad?

396
00:28:02,687 --> 00:28:04,271
We haven’t seen each other yet,

397
00:28:04,272 --> 00:28:06,608
because I haven’t gone home.

398
00:28:07,317 --> 00:28:10,278
For now, I’m staying at the White Hostel

399
00:28:10,570 --> 00:28:12,364
since my classmate has a dorm here.

400
00:28:12,906 --> 00:28:14,698
I won’t be able to go home yet,

401
00:28:14,699 --> 00:28:16,951
maybe not until 7 p.m.

402
00:28:17,577 --> 00:28:18,828
Are you at White Hostel?

403
00:28:19,162 --> 00:28:20,372
What a coincidence.

404
00:28:20,872 --> 00:28:21,915
I’m on my way there.

405
00:28:22,457 --> 00:28:24,042
Are you heading to White Hostel?

406
00:28:24,626 --> 00:28:25,626
Why?

407
00:28:25,752 --> 00:28:27,253
Are you following me?

408
00:28:27,379 --> 00:28:28,380
Following you?

409
00:28:28,588 --> 00:28:29,964
Why would I do that?

410
00:28:30,548 --> 00:28:32,592
Chief Estrada texted me minutes ago.

411
00:28:33,051 --> 00:28:36,096
Something happened in Room 404
of the White Hostel.

412
00:28:36,846 --> 00:28:38,431
He says he needs my help…

413
00:28:39,057 --> 00:28:40,057
ours.

414
00:28:40,934 --> 00:28:42,435
If you have nothing else to do there,

415
00:28:42,977 --> 00:28:43,977
you can join me.

416
00:28:44,813 --> 00:28:45,813
I’ll see you.

417
00:29:24,602 --> 00:29:25,602
Lori!

418
00:29:25,854 --> 00:29:26,938
Chief Estrada!

419
00:29:28,523 --> 00:29:30,900
You got here fast! Where’s Loki?

420
00:29:31,609 --> 00:29:32,609
Huh?

421
00:29:32,986 --> 00:29:34,028
I said,

422
00:29:34,446 --> 00:29:36,156
you got here fast.

423
00:29:37,782 --> 00:29:40,618
It’s just a coincidence that I’m here.

424
00:29:41,286 --> 00:29:45,373
My classmate who stays here and I
were doing an assignment.

425
00:29:46,458 --> 00:29:48,126
As for Loki…

426
00:29:48,376 --> 00:29:49,836
he’s on the way.

427
00:29:50,378 --> 00:29:52,505
He called me earlier.

428
00:29:54,382 --> 00:29:55,550
Is that so?

429
00:30:01,264 --> 00:30:02,348
Are you okay?

430
00:30:03,016 --> 00:30:04,016
Yes.

431
00:30:06,227 --> 00:30:07,979
Nope. I mean...

432
00:30:09,230 --> 00:30:11,357
I don’t know what I’ll feel.

433
00:30:12,650 --> 00:30:13,818
It's because…

434
00:30:15,111 --> 00:30:17,489
I just can't believe...

435
00:30:18,281 --> 00:30:19,991
that’s there’s another murder...

436
00:30:20,742 --> 00:30:21,742
again.

437
00:30:21,910 --> 00:30:22,994
I know.

438
00:30:23,995 --> 00:30:25,954
These kinds of cases
seem to be happening more.

439
00:30:25,955 --> 00:30:27,499
There were similar ones before.

440
00:30:27,790 --> 00:30:29,709
I thought they stopped, but...

441
00:30:30,001 --> 00:30:31,794
maybe they just took a break.

442
00:30:32,879 --> 00:30:35,215
Rhea, the last member I had,

443
00:30:35,548 --> 00:30:38,468
was killed because she was linked to me.

444
00:30:38,968 --> 00:30:40,677
It’s my responsibility

445
00:30:40,678 --> 00:30:43,723
to look for M and bring him to justice!

446
00:30:44,349 --> 00:30:46,184
Anyway, be careful.

447
00:30:46,601 --> 00:30:48,686
It’s not safe around here anymore.

448
00:30:49,979 --> 00:30:51,564
Well, I’ll go ahead.

449
00:30:51,773 --> 00:30:54,067
When Loki arrives, just follow me.

450
00:30:54,567 --> 00:30:55,610
Alright.

451
00:30:57,570 --> 00:31:00,572
Go to your rooms.
No one goes out, alright?

452
00:31:00,573 --> 00:31:02,242
Just don't go out.

453
00:31:03,535 --> 00:31:05,911
So, what do we have here?

454
00:31:05,912 --> 00:31:08,873
What’s with you?
Why do you suddenly show up?

455
00:31:09,791 --> 00:31:10,874
How convenient for you

456
00:31:10,875 --> 00:31:13,710
to be a few doors away
from the crime scene, huh?

457
00:31:13,711 --> 00:31:15,004
Convenient?

458
00:31:15,755 --> 00:31:16,965
What’s wrong with you, Loki?

459
00:31:17,590 --> 00:31:20,510
How is it convenient for me
to be near a crime scene?

460
00:31:20,718 --> 00:31:23,888
Is it convenient
that I’m near the murder scene?

461
00:31:25,431 --> 00:31:27,933
You know, maybe I should’ve just gone home

462
00:31:27,934 --> 00:31:29,894
and endured the meeting with Papa.

463
00:31:31,437 --> 00:31:34,691
Lorelei, this is not the time
to dwell on 'what ifs.'

464
00:31:35,441 --> 00:31:36,484
You’re already here.

465
00:31:37,485 --> 00:31:39,987
Might as well, help me solve this case.

466
00:31:39,988 --> 00:31:43,866
Does the Q.E.D. Club have to get involved
in every murder case?

467
00:31:44,450 --> 00:31:45,192
I still have a lot to do...

468
00:31:45,217 --> 00:31:47,288
Whatever trivial task
you’re doing can wait.

469
00:31:49,122 --> 00:31:50,331
Just a reminder.

470
00:31:51,708 --> 00:31:53,376
You’re a member of the Q.E.D. Club.

471
00:31:54,752 --> 00:31:56,462
Chief Estrada needs our help.

472
00:31:57,088 --> 00:31:59,256
And we need to help the campus police,

473
00:31:59,257 --> 00:32:02,427
so we can bring justice to the victims.

474
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:03,760
Understood?

475
00:32:19,110 --> 00:32:20,528
Excuse me, miss.

476
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:24,407
I’m Lorelei Rios from the Q.E.D. Club.

477
00:32:24,907 --> 00:32:26,868
May I know your name?

478
00:32:28,494 --> 00:32:29,703
Eunice.

479
00:32:29,704 --> 00:32:31,414
Eunice? Okay.

480
00:32:31,748 --> 00:32:35,084
Is it okay if I interview you
about what happened?

481
00:32:35,752 --> 00:32:37,712
Please tell me anything that you know.

482
00:32:38,630 --> 00:32:39,672
No pressure.

483
00:32:44,469 --> 00:32:46,804
What’s your relation to the victim?

484
00:32:47,889 --> 00:32:49,098
What’s her name?

485
00:32:50,808 --> 00:32:52,852
Her... her name is Janine.

486
00:32:54,687 --> 00:32:56,147
She is my friend.

487
00:32:58,816 --> 00:33:00,818
We’re dormmates.

488
00:33:02,070 --> 00:33:03,696
You know, more often than not,

489
00:33:04,238 --> 00:33:06,449
the person who first discovers the body...

490
00:33:06,866 --> 00:33:08,660
is the culprit.

491
00:33:09,994 --> 00:33:12,163
Believe me,

492
00:33:13,122 --> 00:33:16,124
I couldn't kill my dormmate.

493
00:33:16,125 --> 00:33:18,169
I could never do that.

494
00:33:18,961 --> 00:33:20,213
I believe you.

495
00:33:20,505 --> 00:33:22,423
I just got home when...

496
00:33:22,882 --> 00:33:26,177
when I saw her lifeless...

497
00:33:27,720 --> 00:33:28,845
I believe you.

498
00:33:28,846 --> 00:33:29,846
- Okay?
- Chief.

499
00:33:30,473 --> 00:33:32,642
Please forgive my companion.

500
00:33:32,809 --> 00:33:34,185
He just wants to help.

501
00:33:38,314 --> 00:33:41,233
Do you know someone
who could’ve done this to her?

502
00:33:41,234 --> 00:33:42,234
One more. Yeah.

503
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:44,820
Yes.

504
00:33:45,863 --> 00:33:47,990
I saw she posted something yesterday.

505
00:33:49,158 --> 00:33:52,578
Because she broke up
with her ex-boyfriend.

506
00:33:53,413 --> 00:33:56,082
- Yeah, thank you.
- Since she wants to focus on her studies.

507
00:33:57,125 --> 00:33:58,251
The problem is,

508
00:34:00,002 --> 00:34:02,672
her ex didn’t like it.

509
00:34:04,424 --> 00:34:05,675
So what happened is...

510
00:34:06,426 --> 00:34:09,095
he suddenly grabbed my friend,

511
00:34:09,721 --> 00:34:13,516
and forced a kiss on her at their campus.

512
00:34:15,810 --> 00:34:19,147
Next time, don't let them know
that you trust them.

513
00:34:19,605 --> 00:34:24,359
Remember, in a murder case,
everyone is a suspect.

514
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:25,694
I know that.

515
00:34:25,695 --> 00:34:28,656
But you could see
how upset she was earlier, right?

516
00:34:28,906 --> 00:34:30,700
And you still accused her.

517
00:34:31,534 --> 00:34:34,162
Our decisions must be grounded in facts,

518
00:34:34,662 --> 00:34:36,288
and supported by evidence.

519
00:34:36,289 --> 00:34:38,708
Loki, there’s nothing wrong
with having empathy.

520
00:34:39,041 --> 00:34:40,626
And what if she’s innocent?

521
00:34:41,252 --> 00:34:43,421
We’d just be making her trauma worse.

522
00:34:44,672 --> 00:34:47,008
It’s so painful to lose a friend.

523
00:34:48,342 --> 00:34:50,511
You of all people should understand that.

524
00:34:53,639 --> 00:34:55,099
Lori! Loki!

525
00:34:55,391 --> 00:34:56,434
Please come here!

526
00:35:20,374 --> 00:35:22,168
I really hate seeing that pose.

527
00:35:27,340 --> 00:35:30,301
- This is Officer Bastien Montreal.
- Chief.

528
00:35:31,010 --> 00:35:32,177
- Rookie officer.
- Hi.

529
00:35:32,178 --> 00:35:35,056
This is Lori and Loki of Q.E.D. Club.

530
00:35:35,765 --> 00:35:37,767
They help out with the investigations.

531
00:35:38,851 --> 00:35:40,435
Hi! Nice meeting you.

532
00:35:40,436 --> 00:35:42,772
I heard a lot about you and your club.

533
00:35:43,272 --> 00:35:45,233
I’m glad I finally get to work with you.

534
00:35:45,525 --> 00:35:47,360
Nice meeting you too, officer.

535
00:35:48,027 --> 00:35:49,612
We recently worked together.

536
00:35:49,862 --> 00:35:52,364
Remember Isaac’s case
from the Lavoisier Club?

537
00:35:52,365 --> 00:35:55,201
- Oh, yeah. He was in the chem lab.
- Chief.

538
00:35:55,868 --> 00:35:58,704
Anyway, this is Janine Montemayor,

539
00:35:58,996 --> 00:36:00,456
name of our victim.

540
00:36:00,915 --> 00:36:02,750
Twenty-two years old,

541
00:36:03,251 --> 00:36:05,043
Tourism major.

542
00:36:05,044 --> 00:36:06,295
The body is still warm.

543
00:36:06,712 --> 00:36:08,964
Rigor mortis hasn’t set in yet.

544
00:36:08,965 --> 00:36:12,552
We estimate it’s been less than an hour
since she was killed.

545
00:36:13,219 --> 00:36:17,473
We dusted the murder weapon
for fingerprints,

546
00:36:17,974 --> 00:36:19,517
we didn’t find anything.

547
00:36:20,059 --> 00:36:25,189
Looks like the suspect
cleaned the knife well,

548
00:36:25,690 --> 00:36:29,402
because it was wet
when we found it in the sink.

549
00:36:31,070 --> 00:36:32,113
Your thoughts?

550
00:36:34,991 --> 00:36:37,243
The girl outside who found the body…

551
00:36:38,119 --> 00:36:39,954
did not kill the unfortunate victim.

552
00:36:40,955 --> 00:36:42,039
If she did,

553
00:36:42,999 --> 00:36:45,084
blood would have splattered
on her school uniform.

554
00:36:47,086 --> 00:36:48,086
And…

555
00:36:48,629 --> 00:36:50,381
it’s impossible for her to change

556
00:36:50,923 --> 00:36:53,426
and ditch the bloody clothes so quickly.

557
00:36:54,510 --> 00:36:57,430
So there’s a chance that Eunice is right?

558
00:36:58,931 --> 00:37:01,851
And it's Janine’s ex-boyfriend
who's behind this?

559
00:37:04,937 --> 00:37:05,937
Possible!

560
00:37:07,565 --> 00:37:11,527
Judging by the multiple stab wounds
the victim’s body has sustained...

561
00:37:12,945 --> 00:37:14,030
the killer

562
00:37:14,530 --> 00:37:16,616
must have a deep grudge against her.

563
00:37:19,619 --> 00:37:20,912
Having a broken heart

564
00:37:21,746 --> 00:37:23,497
can be a vicious motive

565
00:37:23,915 --> 00:37:24,916
for murder.

566
00:37:27,668 --> 00:37:31,088
I got the logbook the guard was holding
this afternoon.

567
00:37:31,464 --> 00:37:35,675
And we took pictures of the recent page

568
00:37:35,676 --> 00:37:37,720
of log-ins in the log book.

569
00:37:38,346 --> 00:37:39,221
Lori,

570
00:37:39,222 --> 00:37:40,514
you arrived here at…

571
00:37:41,766 --> 00:37:44,060
4:21 p.m.

572
00:37:44,977 --> 00:37:46,270
The crime happened,

573
00:37:46,562 --> 00:37:49,398
between 4 and 5 p.m.

574
00:37:50,316 --> 00:37:55,029
These three names fit the time frame

575
00:37:55,363 --> 00:37:57,615
when they met Janine.

576
00:37:57,949 --> 00:37:59,909
So, we have...

577
00:38:00,284 --> 00:38:04,162
David Florencio, Richmond Montero
and Christopher Bautista.

578
00:38:04,163 --> 00:38:06,248
I’m calling them in for questioning.

579
00:38:08,542 --> 00:38:11,420
Your log-in time
matches David’s log-out time.

580
00:38:13,381 --> 00:38:14,840
Did you notice anything earlier?

581
00:38:21,555 --> 00:38:24,558
Yes, I think I noticed him.

582
00:38:25,101 --> 00:38:28,688
I didn’t see his face clearly,
but he wore a gray shirt.

583
00:38:29,563 --> 00:38:33,901
Okay. At least we can confirm
that this David entered the premises.

584
00:38:35,152 --> 00:38:38,906
Shards on the floor.
Probably from a shattered glass.

585
00:39:06,225 --> 00:39:07,977
Aren’t you going to answer that call?

586
00:39:08,936 --> 00:39:13,441
It’s better if he thinks I’m busy,
that’s why I’m not answering.

587
00:39:14,567 --> 00:39:17,111
Anyway, what are the findings?

588
00:39:19,697 --> 00:39:20,697
Well...

589
00:39:21,532 --> 00:39:23,492
what can you say
about that glass of water?

590
00:39:40,801 --> 00:39:43,604
The water is still cold, even without ice.

591
00:39:46,932 --> 00:39:48,642
The AC isn't even on.

592
00:39:50,102 --> 00:39:51,103
Your thoughts?

593
00:39:53,154 --> 00:39:56,282
Janine put ice cubes in both glasses.

594
00:39:57,818 --> 00:40:00,696
She offered that glass
to her possible killer.

595
00:40:01,238 --> 00:40:02,947
Then something hit a glass,

596
00:40:02,948 --> 00:40:05,659
so it broke
and scattered shards all over.

597
00:40:06,786 --> 00:40:08,412
No force of entry.

598
00:40:09,288 --> 00:40:12,625
So does it mean, she knows her killer?

599
00:40:16,378 --> 00:40:19,423
We have little to no doubt
about that angle.

600
00:40:20,549 --> 00:40:23,385
The question is, of the three visitors…

601
00:40:24,762 --> 00:40:27,555
which one of them
will the victim let into her room

602
00:40:27,556 --> 00:40:29,391
and give cold water?

603
00:40:36,148 --> 00:40:38,484
Christopher Bautista, right?

604
00:40:38,734 --> 00:40:39,734
Yes.

605
00:40:39,944 --> 00:40:43,739
According to the victim’s roommate,
Eunice,

606
00:40:44,031 --> 00:40:46,617
you supposedly had a motive
to kill Janine.

607
00:40:46,909 --> 00:40:50,412
You’re forcing her to get back with you,
even though she doesn’t want to.

608
00:40:50,871 --> 00:40:51,956
Just because of that?

609
00:40:52,581 --> 00:40:54,416
That’s such a shallow reason.

610
00:40:54,792 --> 00:40:59,171
Just because she won’t get back with me
doesn’t mean I’d kill her.

611
00:40:59,797 --> 00:41:03,591
If you have any suspicions,
ask Richmond.

612
00:41:03,592 --> 00:41:05,845
Or that jerk, David.

613
00:41:06,470 --> 00:41:09,473
Janine and I have been close friends
since elementary.

614
00:41:09,932 --> 00:41:14,103
If we have misunderstandings,
we talk them out.

615
00:41:14,687 --> 00:41:16,605
I won’t let it happen in a brutal way.

616
00:41:17,064 --> 00:41:18,399
What, close friends?

617
00:41:18,732 --> 00:41:20,092
He's waiting for her to be single.

618
00:41:20,401 --> 00:41:23,696
Even when Janine and I were together,
she still hung around Janine.

619
00:41:24,113 --> 00:41:26,281
Janine told me last week.

620
00:41:26,282 --> 00:41:29,910
That jerk confessed his feelings to her.

621
00:41:30,744 --> 00:41:34,665
But Janine said,
"The feeling's not mutual."

622
00:41:35,291 --> 00:41:38,836
That’s true,
I confessed to Janine last week.

623
00:41:39,461 --> 00:41:42,256
But she only offered me friendship.

624
00:41:42,548 --> 00:41:44,216
And I was satisfied with that.

625
00:41:44,758 --> 00:41:49,388
I was actually happy that our friendship
didn’t get awkward after I confessed.

626
00:41:49,930 --> 00:41:53,058
So what’s David Florencio’s involvement?

627
00:41:53,934 --> 00:41:56,979
Janine told me
she seems to have a stalker.

628
00:41:57,104 --> 00:41:58,313
Someone who follows her

629
00:41:58,314 --> 00:42:02,484
from when she leaves for school
until she gets home.

630
00:42:03,235 --> 00:42:05,905
Oh, they say you're Janine's stalker.

631
00:42:07,239 --> 00:42:12,912
Last week, I saw that guy
following Janine three times.

632
00:42:13,412 --> 00:42:14,412
Maybe…

633
00:42:14,705 --> 00:42:16,415
he's the one who killed my girlfriend.

634
00:42:16,749 --> 00:42:19,210
Correction,
she’s already his ex-girlfriend.

635
00:42:19,543 --> 00:42:21,879
So, why did you visit the victim?

636
00:42:23,047 --> 00:42:24,256
According to the logbook,

637
00:42:24,548 --> 00:42:28,636
David logged in at 4:05 p.m.,

638
00:42:28,886 --> 00:42:32,431
and logged out at 4:21 p.m.

639
00:42:32,932 --> 00:42:37,102
That's enough time
to commit a serious crime.

640
00:42:37,770 --> 00:42:39,355
So, am I right?

641
00:42:40,606 --> 00:42:42,191
I went to Room 404

642
00:42:42,733 --> 00:42:44,151
to introduce myself to Janine.

643
00:42:44,652 --> 00:42:47,905
Yeah, I’ve been tailing her
wherever she goes for a while now.

644
00:42:48,447 --> 00:42:52,284
But I don’t want to hide
in the dark anymore.

645
00:42:52,701 --> 00:42:55,788
I didn’t want her to be scared anymore,
so I went to see her here.

646
00:42:56,664 --> 00:42:58,999
Then when you knocked,
she opened the door,

647
00:42:59,250 --> 00:43:01,585
asked you to come in,
and offered you a glass of water.

648
00:43:02,002 --> 00:43:04,630
And that’s when you stabbed her
multiple times, right?

649
00:43:05,256 --> 00:43:06,256
No!

650
00:43:06,674 --> 00:43:07,674
I did knock,

651
00:43:07,925 --> 00:43:08,925
but...

652
00:43:09,093 --> 00:43:10,427
she didn’t open the door.

653
00:43:11,303 --> 00:43:12,638
I knew she was there,

654
00:43:13,055 --> 00:43:14,181
so I waited.

655
00:43:14,890 --> 00:43:19,311
But after a few minutes
and she still didn’t come out, I left.

656
00:43:19,728 --> 00:43:25,233
Next to log in was Richmond at 4:24 p.m.,

657
00:43:25,234 --> 00:43:29,154
and he left at 4:40.

658
00:43:29,655 --> 00:43:35,244
What did you do here in those 16 minutes?

659
00:43:36,078 --> 00:43:39,039
I just came from the gym
before coming here to the hostel.

660
00:43:39,164 --> 00:43:41,458
Because Janine and I
had an assignment to work on.

661
00:43:42,042 --> 00:43:44,962
When I knocked, she didn’t answer.

662
00:43:45,421 --> 00:43:49,258
I only waited a few minutes.
She might have gone out to buy something.

663
00:43:49,883 --> 00:43:52,011
After ten minutes, I left.

664
00:43:52,511 --> 00:43:55,597
The last to log in was Christopher,

665
00:43:55,931 --> 00:44:00,185
4:44 p.m., and he left at 4:59.

666
00:44:00,769 --> 00:44:02,062
So, what’s your story?

667
00:44:03,188 --> 00:44:08,610
I tried calling Janine around 4:30 p.m.

668
00:44:08,944 --> 00:44:12,197
I just tried, but she didn’t answer.

669
00:44:12,948 --> 00:44:17,786
But after five minutes,
I got a text from her.

670
00:44:22,333 --> 00:44:26,795
So the moment I read her message,
I rushed straight here.

671
00:44:27,838 --> 00:44:30,591
Because I just want
to make things right with her.

672
00:44:30,924 --> 00:44:34,678
I knocked so many times,
but she wouldn’t open the door.

673
00:44:35,387 --> 00:44:37,306
No one was talking inside either.

674
00:44:37,681 --> 00:44:41,810
I kept shouting and apologizing
at the door.

675
00:44:42,019 --> 00:44:44,021
But still nothing.

676
00:44:45,147 --> 00:44:48,150
So maybe she changed her mind.

677
00:44:48,859 --> 00:44:49,859
So, that’s it...

678
00:44:50,402 --> 00:44:51,612
I just went home.

679
00:44:55,699 --> 00:44:57,576
Based on their statements,

680
00:44:57,951 --> 00:45:01,162
none of them saw Janine

681
00:45:01,163 --> 00:45:03,999
when they went to Room 404.

682
00:45:05,709 --> 00:45:11,340
At that time, you were inside
your classmate’s room, Room 402.

683
00:45:11,924 --> 00:45:14,760
Didn't you notice any...

684
00:45:15,844 --> 00:45:17,054
noise?

685
00:45:19,098 --> 00:45:21,016
Sorry, chief. Nothing, really.

686
00:45:21,892 --> 00:45:22,935
But, chief...

687
00:45:23,769 --> 00:45:25,979
if one of them is the culprit,

688
00:45:26,313 --> 00:45:29,900
that means one of them is lying.

689
00:45:31,860 --> 00:45:32,860
Chief,

690
00:45:33,570 --> 00:45:35,780
don’t they have
a security camera installed

691
00:45:35,781 --> 00:45:38,283
on every floor of the hostel?

692
00:45:38,951 --> 00:45:39,951
You know,

693
00:45:40,244 --> 00:45:41,828
I asked the guard.

694
00:45:41,829 --> 00:45:43,122
You know what he said?

695
00:45:43,455 --> 00:45:45,582
The CCTV on the 4th floor is broken.

696
00:45:45,874 --> 00:45:48,585
It’s scheduled to be fixed tomorrow.

697
00:45:50,796 --> 00:45:52,548
How convenient for the killer!

698
00:45:54,466 --> 00:45:56,760
But, unfortunately, for him…

699
00:45:59,430 --> 00:46:01,849
I have an idea of who he might be.

700
00:46:03,684 --> 00:46:05,227
Really? Who?

701
00:46:12,234 --> 00:46:13,360
So… what now?

702
00:46:13,694 --> 00:46:15,696
Does that mean all three of them
will go to jail?

703
00:46:16,613 --> 00:46:19,491
Looks like two of them
are telling the truth.

704
00:46:20,033 --> 00:46:21,243
And one of them isn’t.

705
00:46:22,119 --> 00:46:24,204
Poor two who have nothing to do with this.

706
00:46:25,497 --> 00:46:26,497
Just wait.

707
00:46:27,082 --> 00:46:28,125
We’re not yet done.

708
00:46:29,042 --> 00:46:30,169
Follow me.

709
00:46:36,383 --> 00:46:37,718
So you heard it?

710
00:46:38,352 --> 00:46:39,353
I did.

711
00:46:41,138 --> 00:46:42,514
I have a follow-up question.

712
00:46:43,348 --> 00:46:44,516
What is it now?

713
00:46:45,684 --> 00:46:47,102
Who among you three

714
00:46:47,603 --> 00:46:50,022
would she be most likely
to let inside her room

715
00:46:50,522 --> 00:46:52,274
and offer a glass of water to?

716
00:46:55,736 --> 00:46:57,237
Didn't I tell you earlier?

717
00:46:57,738 --> 00:46:59,281
I didn’t get in.

718
00:46:59,698 --> 00:47:00,698
Me too!

719
00:47:01,325 --> 00:47:02,451
Even worse for me.

720
00:47:05,037 --> 00:47:06,121
This means…

721
00:47:06,705 --> 00:47:07,998
one of you lied earlier.

722
00:47:09,958 --> 00:47:13,378
One of you knocked on the victim’s door.

723
00:47:15,609 --> 00:47:18,550
She let that person in,
completely unaware,

724
00:47:18,954 --> 00:47:20,613
about what he might be capable of.

725
00:47:22,679 --> 00:47:23,679
So...

726
00:47:24,496 --> 00:47:25,664
who could that person be?

727
00:47:27,048 --> 00:47:28,091
Could it be you...

728
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:29,853
David Florencio?

729
00:47:31,188 --> 00:47:34,942
The suspicious stalker
who had been following her?

730
00:47:36,777 --> 00:47:37,777
No!

731
00:47:38,654 --> 00:47:41,240
Janine maybe aware of your presence...

732
00:47:41,907 --> 00:47:44,743
but she did not know anything about you.

733
00:47:48,497 --> 00:47:50,415
She would not open a door

734
00:47:50,749 --> 00:47:52,084
to any stranger.

735
00:47:53,126 --> 00:47:54,503
She would not let you in.

736
00:47:56,046 --> 00:47:59,049
And she would not offer you
a glass of water.

737
00:48:01,677 --> 00:48:02,803
Maybe it’s you...

738
00:48:04,012 --> 00:48:05,722
Christopher Bautista.

739
00:48:06,974 --> 00:48:08,308
The ex-boyfriend.

740
00:48:10,561 --> 00:48:14,439
You attempted to kiss Janine
even after your breakup.

741
00:48:15,440 --> 00:48:18,110
Janine would not even think
of inviting you in.

742
00:48:18,610 --> 00:48:19,820
She’d rather tell you

743
00:48:20,362 --> 00:48:21,405
to go to hell.

744
00:48:22,906 --> 00:48:25,450
But why did she text me…

745
00:48:25,867 --> 00:48:27,286
wanting to talk to me?

746
00:48:29,746 --> 00:48:31,122
It’s a trick used by the culprit

747
00:48:31,123 --> 00:48:33,500
to make us think
that the victim is still alive

748
00:48:33,792 --> 00:48:37,713
by the time she messaged you
at around 4:35 p.m.

749
00:48:43,885 --> 00:48:44,885
That’s right!

750
00:48:45,304 --> 00:48:48,015
The culprit is none other than the person

751
00:48:48,348 --> 00:48:50,225
who went inside the victim’s room

752
00:48:50,851 --> 00:48:54,563
between 4:24 p.m. and 4:40 p.m.

753
00:48:55,606 --> 00:48:56,857
Her best friend...

754
00:48:57,357 --> 00:48:59,150
Richmond Montero.

755
00:48:59,151 --> 00:49:01,360
No… No, that’s not true.

756
00:49:01,361 --> 00:49:02,237
You’re wrong!

757
00:49:02,238 --> 00:49:04,156
What you’re saying isn’t true!

758
00:49:04,615 --> 00:49:05,991
That’s not true!

759
00:49:06,366 --> 00:49:07,992
Don’t believe him!

760
00:49:07,993 --> 00:49:09,328
Among the three of you,

761
00:49:10,203 --> 00:49:12,914
you’re the only one in good terms
with Janine, right?

762
00:49:15,292 --> 00:49:16,793
You mentioned earlier…

763
00:49:17,210 --> 00:49:18,462
that you’re close friends.

764
00:49:19,046 --> 00:49:20,964
And your relationship didn’t change,

765
00:49:21,465 --> 00:49:23,175
even after you admitted your feelings.

766
00:49:24,926 --> 00:49:27,012
There’s no doubt
that she would open the door

767
00:49:27,554 --> 00:49:30,474
let you in
and offer you a glass of water.

768
00:49:30,849 --> 00:49:33,518
You know,
if what you’re accusing is true…

769
00:49:34,519 --> 00:49:35,937
why would I kill her?

770
00:49:36,229 --> 00:49:37,229
Huh?

771
00:49:37,314 --> 00:49:38,356
What?

772
00:49:38,357 --> 00:49:41,234
I’d just stab her for no reason?

773
00:49:41,985 --> 00:49:45,072
What if you saw an opportunity

774
00:49:45,447 --> 00:49:47,240
in her breakup with Christopher?

775
00:49:48,116 --> 00:49:49,242
You think,

776
00:49:49,701 --> 00:49:52,954
you can already play the role
of Janine’s boyfriend?

777
00:49:53,413 --> 00:49:54,498
The problem is,

778
00:49:54,790 --> 00:49:56,249
even after their breakup,

779
00:49:56,917 --> 00:49:59,878
she still can’t return your feelings.

780
00:50:01,129 --> 00:50:03,882
Because she doesn’t feel anything for you.

781
00:50:05,008 --> 00:50:06,134
It’s possible

782
00:50:06,635 --> 00:50:08,220
you went blind with rage,

783
00:50:08,720 --> 00:50:10,347
grabbed a knife,

784
00:50:10,847 --> 00:50:13,725
and kept stabbing her.

785
00:50:15,560 --> 00:50:16,895
You jerk!

786
00:50:17,062 --> 00:50:18,980
I’ll smash your face!

787
00:50:19,940 --> 00:50:22,025
Believe whatever you want!

788
00:50:22,567 --> 00:50:24,569
But you have no evidence against me!

789
00:50:25,195 --> 00:50:26,195
It’s on you.

790
00:50:26,530 --> 00:50:27,781
You’re talking nonsense!

791
00:50:28,073 --> 00:50:29,073
Crazy!

792
00:50:29,282 --> 00:50:31,367
Take off your shoes and show the soles

793
00:50:31,368 --> 00:50:33,704
- to everyone in this lobby.
- Hold it, hold it by the foot!

794
00:50:40,001 --> 00:50:41,503
After killing Janine…

795
00:50:42,379 --> 00:50:45,674
you accidentally stepped
on a shard of glass near the table.

796
00:50:47,517 --> 00:50:48,893
You were in such a rush,

797
00:50:49,261 --> 00:50:50,512
you didn’t notice.

798
00:50:51,555 --> 00:50:53,432
When the police ask you to come here,

799
00:50:53,849 --> 00:50:55,642
you’re not allowed to enter the room.

800
00:50:56,109 --> 00:50:58,862
So how did this shard get in here?

801
00:50:59,229 --> 00:51:01,940
But there isn’t a single trace of blood
on the clothes, Loki.

802
00:51:02,437 --> 00:51:04,773
He already changed
before leaving the unit.

803
00:51:05,576 --> 00:51:07,661
He said that he went to the gym earlier,

804
00:51:08,029 --> 00:51:10,073
so he must have brought extra clothes…

805
00:51:11,111 --> 00:51:12,111
with him.

806
00:51:12,951 --> 00:51:16,371
If the shard stuck in the sole
of his right shoe is not enough,

807
00:51:16,663 --> 00:51:18,081
we have to review

808
00:51:18,623 --> 00:51:22,919
security footage in the lobby
by the time when he went out

809
00:51:23,545 --> 00:51:24,546
and he went in.

810
00:51:25,672 --> 00:51:27,966
You’ll also notice
the change of his clothes.

811
00:51:28,175 --> 00:51:30,134
And you can also run a luminol test

812
00:51:30,135 --> 00:51:32,846
on his shoes to check
if there are traces of blood.

813
00:51:37,347 --> 00:51:39,349
I have nowhere else to go.

814
00:51:39,478 --> 00:51:40,771
- Let’s go?
- Okay.

815
00:51:41,396 --> 00:51:44,774
The nice thing about White Hostel
is you can have visitors.

816
00:51:44,775 --> 00:51:46,061
Please sign in, sir.

817
00:51:50,071 --> 00:51:52,199
I lost control when it happened.

818
00:51:52,866 --> 00:51:55,034
- I love Janine. Believe me.
- You have the right to remain silent.

819
00:51:55,035 --> 00:51:56,494
- Hold him! Hold him!
- Any statement you make

820
00:51:56,495 --> 00:51:57,287
may be used for against you

821
00:51:57,288 --> 00:51:59,608
- in any court of law in the Philippines.
- I didn't mean to!

822
00:52:00,123 --> 00:52:02,583
- You have the right...
- I love Janine!

823
00:52:02,584 --> 00:52:04,710
to have a competent and independent
counsel preferably of your own choice.

824
00:52:04,711 --> 00:52:07,296
If you cannot afford
the services of counsel,

825
00:52:07,297 --> 00:52:10,382
- the government will provide one for you.
- Chief! I love Janine!

826
00:52:10,383 --> 00:52:12,259
- You have the right to choose...
- Chief!

827
00:52:12,260 --> 00:52:15,888
an independent and competent doctor
to have a physical examination.

828
00:52:15,889 --> 00:52:17,139
It's not my fault!

829
00:52:17,140 --> 00:52:18,849
If you can't afford
the services of a doctor,

830
00:52:18,850 --> 00:52:22,062
- the state shall provide one for you.
- I didn’t mean to!

831
00:52:22,395 --> 00:52:24,731
Do you understand these rights?

832
00:52:27,234 --> 00:52:29,611
- Go inside!
- Sir, I didn’t mean to!

833
00:52:31,738 --> 00:52:33,031
Sir!

834
00:52:34,866 --> 00:52:36,952
I didn't mean to!

835
00:52:38,495 --> 00:52:40,288
I love Janine!

836
00:52:40,831 --> 00:52:42,582
I love her so much!

837
00:52:50,966 --> 00:52:52,509
Thanks a lot, guys!

838
00:52:53,885 --> 00:52:55,762
The Q.E.D. Club was really helpful.

839
00:52:55,971 --> 00:52:57,597
We owe you so much already.

840
00:52:57,931 --> 00:52:59,975
Anytime, Chief Estrada.

841
00:53:06,356 --> 00:53:07,356
By the way, chief,

842
00:53:07,357 --> 00:53:10,652
is there any updates
on the missing chemicals on the chem lab?

843
00:53:11,278 --> 00:53:12,278
Yes.

844
00:53:12,404 --> 00:53:14,780
According to the property custodian,

845
00:53:14,781 --> 00:53:18,785
so many bottles
of sodium hydroxide went missing.

846
00:53:20,245 --> 00:53:21,829
What we don’t get

847
00:53:21,830 --> 00:53:25,292
is why a student would be interested

848
00:53:25,750 --> 00:53:29,087
in a chemical used as drain cleaner.

849
00:53:29,796 --> 00:53:31,715
Sodium hydroxide?

850
00:53:32,549 --> 00:53:35,468
What is M’s plan
on this chemical compound?

851
00:53:37,262 --> 00:53:38,263
Anyway...

852
00:53:39,139 --> 00:53:41,140
I’ll keep you posted for further updates.

853
00:53:41,141 --> 00:53:45,144
And I need to go,
I have to get back to the station

854
00:53:45,145 --> 00:53:47,480
to get Richmond’s confession, alright?

855
00:53:48,982 --> 00:53:49,982
- Thanks again, guys!
- Alright.

856
00:53:49,983 --> 00:53:50,983
Thanks, chief.

857
00:53:51,443 --> 00:53:53,486
- Thanks, chief.
- Gentlemen.

858
00:53:57,282 --> 00:53:58,950
Lori! Girl!

859
00:53:59,242 --> 00:54:00,410
Are you going home now?

860
00:54:00,744 --> 00:54:01,994
You didn’t even tell me.

861
00:54:01,995 --> 00:54:03,662
You said you were just going
to check something.

862
00:54:03,663 --> 00:54:05,539
Your bag’s still in my room.

863
00:54:05,540 --> 00:54:07,834
Yeah. I know, Rosetta. I’m sorry.

864
00:54:08,209 --> 00:54:12,631
I just lost track of time,
so I couldn’t say goodbye.

865
00:54:12,964 --> 00:54:15,592
It’s okay, I get that you’re busy.

866
00:54:17,761 --> 00:54:18,761
And, you...

867
00:54:19,304 --> 00:54:20,388
you’re keeping secrets.

868
00:54:21,097 --> 00:54:25,060
I’d understand if you said
you had Q.E.D. matters to deal with.

869
00:54:28,813 --> 00:54:30,148
Q.E.D.

870
00:54:31,858 --> 00:54:33,568
Lorelei, who’s this girl?

871
00:54:34,778 --> 00:54:37,738
By the way, she's my classmate,
Rosetta Rodriguez.

872
00:54:37,739 --> 00:54:39,074
This is Loki.

873
00:54:39,824 --> 00:54:42,743
I was at her unit earlier when you called.

874
00:54:42,744 --> 00:54:44,412
We were doing an assignment.

875
00:54:46,122 --> 00:54:47,666
Hi, Loki!

876
00:54:50,502 --> 00:54:52,629
So you're the president of Q.E.D.?

877
00:54:52,963 --> 00:54:54,756
I've heard a lot about you.

878
00:54:55,256 --> 00:54:56,298
By the way,

879
00:54:56,299 --> 00:54:58,842
if you need photos for documentation,

880
00:54:58,843 --> 00:55:00,261
I have some on my phone.

881
00:55:00,762 --> 00:55:01,762
Photos?

882
00:55:01,846 --> 00:55:05,850
Earlier I took pictures of you
while you were investigating.

883
00:55:06,142 --> 00:55:07,352
Here, take a look.

884
00:55:08,478 --> 00:55:09,771
This is the first one.

885
00:55:10,063 --> 00:55:11,940
And this is the next one.

886
00:55:12,941 --> 00:55:13,941
There.

887
00:55:18,697 --> 00:55:20,656
I’m planning to submit it
to CU Confessions

888
00:55:20,657 --> 00:55:23,076
so they know your club exists.

889
00:55:23,410 --> 00:55:25,620
Also, kind of like a promotion.

890
00:55:25,954 --> 00:55:27,890
- Wait! Don’t post that!
- It’s perfectly fine with me!

891
00:55:27,914 --> 00:55:28,914
Wait…

892
00:55:29,249 --> 00:55:30,417
is that okay with you?

893
00:55:33,044 --> 00:55:34,586
I don’t like the page,

894
00:55:34,587 --> 00:55:36,339
but I admit they have the following.

895
00:55:37,132 --> 00:55:38,967
If their followers see us in action,

896
00:55:39,509 --> 00:55:41,094
it could attract more clients.

897
00:55:41,261 --> 00:55:44,847
It could also promote Lorelei's blog,

898
00:55:44,848 --> 00:55:46,265
Q.E.D. Chronicles.

899
00:55:46,266 --> 00:55:47,475
You have a blog?

900
00:55:48,935 --> 00:55:52,147
You didn’t say!
I could’ve been reading in my free time.

901
00:55:52,647 --> 00:55:54,232
It’s embarrassing.

902
00:55:54,566 --> 00:55:56,901
I don’t usually owe a favor to anyone,

903
00:55:57,777 --> 00:56:01,031
but we may owe you one
if you’ll do exactly what you’ve said.

904
00:56:01,990 --> 00:56:03,199
Any kind of help

905
00:56:03,825 --> 00:56:06,161
would mean a lot to get our club noticed.

906
00:56:06,703 --> 00:56:07,703
Sure!

907
00:56:08,246 --> 00:56:09,748
My pleasure!

908
00:56:12,876 --> 00:56:13,918
Nice meeting you.

909
00:56:31,227 --> 00:56:35,148
Sorry, I couldn’t go home with you.
I still had to finish our homework.

910
00:56:35,774 --> 00:56:37,067
K.

911
00:56:48,661 --> 00:56:51,705
- Oh, it fell! Lori!
- Oh, Tita!

912
00:56:51,706 --> 00:56:53,165
Why are you just arriving now?

913
00:56:53,166 --> 00:56:55,210
Your dad was waiting earlier.

914
00:56:55,960 --> 00:56:58,128
I told him to wait for you

915
00:56:58,129 --> 00:57:01,049
because you probably have a lot
going on at school.

916
00:57:01,424 --> 00:57:06,054
But he said he needs to go home
to Manila tonight.

917
00:57:07,013 --> 00:57:08,348
I’m sorry, Tita.

918
00:57:08,681 --> 00:57:11,100
We’ve just been really busy with school.

919
00:57:11,101 --> 00:57:12,560
It sure looks like it.

920
00:57:13,228 --> 00:57:14,854
Oh, it's okay.

921
00:57:15,146 --> 00:57:18,942
You better eat dinner with Loki,
then get some rest, okay?

922
00:57:19,192 --> 00:57:21,318
Okay. Thank you, Tita. Goodnight!

923
00:57:21,319 --> 00:57:23,320
Okay... Oh, by the way! By the way!

924
00:57:23,321 --> 00:57:24,781
I almost forgot.

925
00:57:25,615 --> 00:57:30,036
Your dad left a gift for you.
It’s in your room.

926
00:57:32,288 --> 00:57:33,288
Okay.

927
00:58:26,593 --> 00:58:27,593
Ouch!

928
00:58:27,886 --> 00:58:28,886
Sorry!

929
00:58:31,139 --> 00:58:33,141
If you want it you can have it.

930
00:58:35,059 --> 00:58:36,186
Poor teddy bear.

931
00:58:37,103 --> 00:58:39,105
He didn’t deserve to be thrown like that.

932
00:58:39,564 --> 00:58:41,607
If you don’t want it, fine.

933
00:58:41,608 --> 00:58:42,774
Give that to me.

934
00:58:42,775 --> 00:58:45,360
No, you said a minute ago
I can have it if I want it.

935
00:58:45,361 --> 00:58:46,446
And I want it.

936
00:58:47,405 --> 00:58:49,157
It’s mine now, and I’m not giving it back.

937
00:58:50,033 --> 00:58:52,285
Fine. Okay, it’s yours.

938
00:58:53,244 --> 00:58:54,494
In a shocking development,

939
00:58:54,495 --> 00:58:56,455
a kidnapping syndicate member
has confessed,

940
00:58:56,456 --> 00:58:59,375
revealing that a powerful politician
is behind the group.

941
00:58:59,500 --> 00:59:01,710
Authorities have not yet named
the suspect.

942
00:59:01,711 --> 00:59:06,007
The revelation could expose links
between organized crime and politics.

943
00:59:06,799 --> 00:59:08,092
Loki…

944
00:59:09,594 --> 00:59:11,638
Is this normal at your school?

945
00:59:12,764 --> 00:59:16,517
Aren’t you wondering
why there’s a killing like this?

946
00:59:17,685 --> 00:59:19,270
Is someone doing this on purpose?

947
00:59:19,646 --> 00:59:21,397
Are we being played?

948
00:59:22,106 --> 00:59:23,733
What’s really going on?

949
00:59:27,654 --> 00:59:29,697
So that’s why
you’ve been quiet this whole time.

950
00:59:31,241 --> 00:59:33,785
You’ve been bothered
by everything that happened today,

951
00:59:33,952 --> 00:59:34,952
aren’t you?

952
00:59:37,205 --> 00:59:38,331
Just to be clear,

953
00:59:39,082 --> 00:59:41,583
I don’t think that the chem lab case

954
00:59:41,584 --> 00:59:44,128
is connected
to the White Hostel murder case.

955
00:59:44,420 --> 00:59:45,420
Loki,

956
00:59:45,546 --> 00:59:48,174
I don’t care if they’re connected or not.

957
00:59:48,967 --> 00:59:50,301
Because, honestly...

958
00:59:50,760 --> 00:59:52,220
I’m not happy about this.

959
00:59:53,054 --> 00:59:54,847
Consecutive murders, Loki.

960
00:59:55,640 --> 00:59:57,141
Why is this happening?

961
00:59:59,185 --> 01:00:00,728
This is the reason.

962
01:00:01,771 --> 01:00:03,147
And just like him,

963
01:00:03,398 --> 01:00:06,734
there might be someone influential
allowing all of this to happen.

964
01:00:07,443 --> 01:00:08,486
Well, who?

965
01:00:09,362 --> 01:00:12,073
Why is the university
letting this happen?

966
01:00:12,532 --> 01:00:14,033
What actions are they taking?

967
01:00:14,826 --> 01:00:17,745
Isn’t there even a news report about it?

968
01:00:18,538 --> 01:00:21,624
People’s lives are at stake, Loki.

969
01:00:22,583 --> 01:00:24,627
I wish I could answer all your questions.

970
01:00:25,503 --> 01:00:27,046
But I don’t have an answer yet.

971
01:00:28,131 --> 01:00:29,299
Like I said,

972
01:00:30,091 --> 01:00:32,260
not everyone is trustworthy.

973
01:00:32,802 --> 01:00:34,136
We need to be careful

974
01:00:34,137 --> 01:00:36,264
because we don’t know
who we're dealing with.

975
01:00:39,142 --> 01:00:42,812
But that doesn’t mean
I’ll stop trying to find answers.

976
01:00:44,355 --> 01:00:45,481
Even if it’s tough…

977
01:00:46,733 --> 01:00:48,443
I’ll fight for our club.

978
01:00:49,402 --> 01:00:51,154
And I need your help, Lorelei.

979
01:00:51,988 --> 01:00:53,573
We need to stand together

980
01:00:54,032 --> 01:00:55,450
and fight for this,

981
01:00:56,576 --> 01:00:59,162
and strive to uncover the truth.

982
01:01:31,361 --> 01:01:34,654
Janine Montemayor
is the third Clark University student

983
01:01:34,655 --> 01:01:37,075
to be murdered
by a fellow student this week.

984
01:01:37,575 --> 01:01:40,828
One wonders why these crimes happen
to good students.

985
01:01:41,120 --> 01:01:45,792
But the bigger question is,
what turns a good student into a criminal.

986
01:01:50,296 --> 01:01:53,173
An innocent young woman
lost her life today,

987
01:01:53,174 --> 01:01:56,094
a casualty of love
she was unable to return.

988
01:01:56,552 --> 01:01:58,388
A crime of passion.

989
01:02:04,310 --> 01:02:07,145
Humans, tend to trust
those who show us kindness

990
01:02:07,146 --> 01:02:09,649
and those who love us and make us happy...

991
01:02:14,487 --> 01:02:17,030
It becomes impossible
to truly distinguish

992
01:02:17,031 --> 01:02:18,825
who is true and who is not.

993
01:02:19,325 --> 01:02:22,285
Sometimes, the person one trusts the most

994
01:02:22,286 --> 01:02:24,497
is the one who ends up hurting you.

995
01:02:25,289 --> 01:02:28,084
Has the world truly become this dangerous?

996
01:02:29,335 --> 01:02:31,504
Richmond, please.

997
01:02:34,549 --> 01:02:36,466
There’s a popular saying,

998
01:02:36,467 --> 01:02:39,387
"Keep your friends close,
but your enemies closer."

999
01:02:40,054 --> 01:02:41,555
But the question is,

1000
01:02:41,556 --> 01:02:43,558
who poses the greater threat,

1001
01:02:43,933 --> 01:02:46,351
the unknown faces at a distance,

1002
01:02:46,352 --> 01:02:49,021
or the familiar souls closest to us?

1003
01:02:52,608 --> 01:02:54,610
Where are you going?

1004
01:02:56,571 --> 01:02:58,614
Please, Richmond.

1005
01:03:21,471 --> 01:03:23,346
As a colleague once said,

1006
01:03:23,347 --> 01:03:24,848
we need to be cautious

1007
01:03:24,849 --> 01:03:26,433
because sometimes,

1008
01:03:26,434 --> 01:03:29,645
people don’t even realize
who their real enemies are.

1009
01:03:44,160 --> 01:03:47,329
Hey, Lori! You said Q.E.D. will help me...

1010
01:03:47,330 --> 01:03:51,249
- You'll help me with your lovelife.
- Solve the mystery why am I single.

1011
01:03:51,250 --> 01:03:54,085
Yes! Thank you!
Thank you so much! See us again!

1012
01:03:54,086 --> 01:03:55,296
Thank you!

1013
01:03:58,466 --> 01:04:00,635
To be fair to Rosetta’s post,

1014
01:04:01,010 --> 01:04:03,554
a lot of people are asking us for help.

1015
01:04:06,349 --> 01:04:08,768
So, so, so bored.

1016
01:04:08,935 --> 01:04:09,935
Huh?

1017
01:04:10,186 --> 01:04:11,186
You know what…

1018
01:04:13,022 --> 01:04:16,234
we don’t have time
to entertain stupid requests.

1019
01:04:16,609 --> 01:04:18,068
You complain

1020
01:04:18,069 --> 01:04:21,155
like it’s not your fault
we have so many clients.

1021
01:04:21,739 --> 01:04:23,031
Also,

1022
01:04:23,032 --> 01:04:25,618
maybe learn to accept and face this.

1023
01:04:32,208 --> 01:04:33,709
But we’re problem-solvers,

1024
01:04:35,169 --> 01:04:37,046
not love gurus or genies.

1025
01:04:37,463 --> 01:04:38,631
I know.

1026
01:04:38,923 --> 01:04:40,716
But let’s not pick and choose.

1027
01:04:41,133 --> 01:04:43,969
Let's just stay faithful
to the purpose of this club,

1028
01:04:43,970 --> 01:04:46,055
which is to help people.

1029
01:04:51,477 --> 01:04:52,895
Where are you going?

1030
01:04:53,020 --> 01:04:54,313
I’m going to buy coffee.

1031
01:05:23,384 --> 01:05:26,679
It seems like your club
is busy attending to new clients.

1032
01:05:30,266 --> 01:05:31,726
I let myself in,

1033
01:05:33,102 --> 01:05:34,437
I hope you don’t mind.

1034
01:05:35,813 --> 01:05:36,938
Forgive my manners.

1035
01:05:36,939 --> 01:05:38,983
I haven't introduced myself properly.

1036
01:05:39,591 --> 01:05:40,776
My name is Luthor...

1037
01:05:41,360 --> 01:05:42,360
Mendez.

1038
01:05:42,695 --> 01:05:44,196
Loki’s elder brother.

1039
01:05:52,246 --> 01:05:53,331
Luthor.

1040
01:05:53,914 --> 01:05:55,082
Nice to meet you.

1041
01:05:55,625 --> 01:05:56,834
I’m Lorelei.

1042
01:05:58,961 --> 01:06:00,546
Nice to meet you, Lorelei.

1043
01:06:13,601 --> 01:06:14,894
What the hell?

1044
01:06:34,914 --> 01:06:36,749
Did you let this guy inside our clubroom?

1045
01:06:37,124 --> 01:06:39,376
A student named Charles Meliton,

1046
01:06:39,377 --> 01:06:41,586
he has compromising photographs
of my friend.

1047
01:06:41,587 --> 01:06:43,172
And as for you, Lorelei,

1048
01:06:43,673 --> 01:06:45,508
I’d like to get to know you better.

1049
01:06:46,509 --> 01:06:48,302
Hey! What are you doing?

1050
01:06:50,304 --> 01:06:51,931
Meet me at the White Hostel…

1051
01:06:52,098 --> 01:06:53,098
5 p.m.

1052
01:06:57,770 --> 01:06:59,980
We need to figure out a way to get in

1053
01:07:00,189 --> 01:07:01,732
and grab Charles’ phone.

1054
01:07:01,816 --> 01:07:05,778
This is simply repayment
for us not dissolving your club.

1055
01:07:07,154 --> 01:07:08,698
Thank you for meeting me this late.

1056
01:07:08,739 --> 01:07:11,741
More than half a year ago,
my brother investigated several cases

1057
01:07:11,742 --> 01:07:13,869
that connected all to one person.

1058
01:07:14,036 --> 01:07:15,246
Only known as M.

1059
01:07:15,788 --> 01:07:16,580
And you,

1060
01:07:16,581 --> 01:07:18,415
by being Loki’s closest person

1061
01:07:18,416 --> 01:07:20,000
could be the next collateral damage.
